"{\"uid\": \"breitbart.com-sports-2024-07-28-organizers-of-paris-olympics-apologize-parody-last-supper\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Organizers for the Paris Olympics issued an apology to people who were left offended by an LGBTQ parody of the Last Supper during the opening ceremony.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 151, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Thomas Jolly, the artistic director for the Olympics opening ceremony, explained that he had \\\"wanted to send a message of love\\\" and inclusion, and did not have intentions \\\"to be subversive.\\\"\", \"from\": 153, \"to\": 343, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"My wish is not to be subversive, nor to mock or to shock,\\\" JollytoldtheAssociated Press.\", \"from\": 345, \"to\": 434, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Most of all, I wanted to send a message of love, a message of inclusion and not at all to divide.\\\"\", \"from\": 435, \"to\": 534, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Last Supper display,seenduring the Olympics opening ceremony, featured Barbara Butch, a DJ, producer, and LGBTQ activist in the middle, drag queens, and transgender performers on either side of her.\", \"from\": 536, \"to\": 738, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 611, \"end\": 624, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbara_Butch\", \"score\": 0.9999897744159937, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Barbara Butch\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbara_Butch\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbara_Butch\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In response to the parody of the Last Supper, the French Catholic Church's Bishops' Conference of France released a statement that the ceremony had \\\"included scenes in which Christianity was mocked and ridiculed.\\\"\", \"from\": 740, \"to\": 953, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 790, \"end\": 812, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church_in_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French Catholic Church\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church_in_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church_in_France\"}, {\"begin\": 797, \"end\": 812, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 0.9999996643614958, \"rank\": 1.5049578750924936e-07, \"text\": \"Catholic Church\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}, {\"begin\": 838, \"end\": 844, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.8809403973181485, \"rank\": 0.13109068509560504, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 914, \"end\": 926, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9878918830776018, \"rank\": 0.012251645437414787, \"text\": \"Christianity\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"This ceremony unfortunately included scenes in which Christianity was mocked and ridiculed, which we deeply regret,\\\" the organization said in itsstatement.\", \"from\": 955, \"to\": 1111, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1009, \"end\": 1021, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9878918830776018, \"rank\": 0.012251645437414787, \"text\": \"Christianity\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Maria Zakharova, a spokeswoman for the Russian Foreign Ministry and the Anglican Community in Egypt also came out criticizing the Olympics for the opening ceremony, according to the outlet.\", \"from\": 1113, \"to\": 1302, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1113, \"end\": 1128, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maria_Zakharova\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Maria Zakharova\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maria_Zakharova\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maria_Zakharova\"}, {\"begin\": 1152, \"end\": 1176, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ministry_of_Foreign_Affairs_(Russia)\", \"score\": 0.9999999998756266, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Russian Foreign Ministry\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ministry_of_Foreign_Affairs_(Russia)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ministry_of_Foreign_Affairs_(Russia)\"}, {\"begin\": 1185, \"end\": 1193, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anglicanism\", \"score\": 0.7370723262692184, \"rank\": 0.35352557699160936, \"text\": \"Anglican\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anglicanism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anglicanism\"}, {\"begin\": 1207, \"end\": 1212, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Egypt\", \"score\": 0.9992692709283186, \"rank\": 0.0003392466496152965, \"text\": \"Egypt\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Egypt\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Egypt\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Clearly there was never an intention to show disrespect to any religious group,\\\" Anne Descamps, a spokesperson for the 2024 Paris Olympics said in a statement, adding that they had tried to \\\"celebrate community tolerance.\\\"\", \"from\": 1304, \"to\": 1527, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1391, \"end\": 1399, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Baptiste_Descamps\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Descamps\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Baptiste_Descamps\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Baptiste_Descamps\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Descamps added that if people were offended, they were \\\"of course, really, really sorry.\\\"\", \"from\": 1529, \"to\": 1618, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1529, \"end\": 1537, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Baptiste_Descamps\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Descamps\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Baptiste_Descamps\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Baptiste_Descamps\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In addition to the Last Supper parody, the opening ceremonyfeatureda dance display that showed women being \\\"flung around on poles.\\\"\", \"from\": 1620, \"to\": 1751, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Another dance number featured three dancers, a woman and two men, who danced through the streets and were seen going up the stairs of a building, stopping as they began kissing.\", \"from\": 1752, \"to\": 1929, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The three dancers were then seen entering a room as they continued kissing until the door was shut.\", \"from\": 1930, \"to\": 2029, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Pleaselet us knowif you are having issues with commenting.\", \"from\": 2031, \"to\": 2089, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Copyright \\u00a9 2025 Breitbart\", \"from\": 2099, \"to\": 2125, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2116, \"end\": 2125, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Breitbart_News\", \"score\": 0.9999938322338617, \"rank\": 6.167804118074305e-06, \"text\": \"Breitbart\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Breitbart_News\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Breitbart_News\"}]}]}"